  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nRe-entrancyGuard is too linear in nature and there can be case where some functions may want re-entrancy guard to be disabled when called by specfic contract and by default re-entrancy guard to be enabled. For these use cases I am proposing introduction of permissioned re-entrancy guard which facilitates this exact use-case. \r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\nCode for permissioned re-entrancy guard is at this location\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/18dew/6cfcc6eace110291df13c7be34e8c5eb\r\n",
